					<description><![CDATA[If you&#8217;ve ever felt like PhantomJS was too verbose, you may want to try NightmareJS. It is a wrapper around PhantomJS that uses English language style commands: [sourcecode lang=&#8221;js&#8221;] new Nightmare() .goto(&#8216;http://yahoo.com&/#8217;) .type(&#8216;input[title=&#34;Search&#34;]&#8217;, &#8216;github nightmare&#8217;) .click(&#8216;.searchsubmit&#8217;) .run(); [/sourcecode]]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>If you&#8217;ve ever felt like <a href="http://phantomjs.org/">PhantomJS</a> was too verbose, you may want to try <a href="http://www.nightmarejs.org/">NightmareJS</a>.  It is a wrapper around PhantomJS that uses English language style commands:</p>
<p>[sourcecode lang=&#8221;js&#8221;]<br />
new Nightmare()<br />
  .goto(&#8216;http://yahoo.com&/#8217;)<br />
  .type(&#8216;input[title=&quot;Search&quot;]&#8217;, &#8216;github nightmare&#8217;)<br />
  .click(&#8216;.searchsubmit&#8217;)<br />
  .run();<br />
[/sourcecode]</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
